Polysilicon Spot Price Falls 4.7% to $44.40, EnergyTrend Says

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-10-06T07:41:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/polysilicon-spot-price-falls-4-7-to-44-40-energytrend-says.html
The spot price of polysilicon, the
raw material for most solar panels, fell 4.7 percent on the week
to $44.40 per kilogram, EnergyTrend said.  The average selling price of finished panels slid 2.9
percent to $1.09 per watt of peak capacity while multi-silicon
solar cells, the main component of a panel, fell 2.8 percent to
$2.76 each, the Taipei-based research company said in an e-
mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Sills at 
 bsills@bloomberg.net  